<div class="materials-wrapper-section">
  <div class="materials-intro-section">
    <h1 class="home-header">Materials</h1>
    <p>We offer Granite, Quartz and Ceramic worktops in a wide range of styles. You can choose a design from our in-house range or opt for one of our trusted suppliers. Find out more about each of the materials we use by selecting one below:</p>
  </div>
  <div class="material-display-section">
    <div class="materials-tab">
      <ul class="materials-tab-list">
      <li class="selected-material">Granite</li>
      <li>Quartz</li>
      <li>Ceramic</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="materials-granite-section">
      <div class="material-overview">
        <p>Granite is undoubtedly one of the toughest materials on the planet. It is formed through a process which takes millions of years deep beneath the earth's surface. As a result, kitchen granite worktops are an excellent work surface, they're tough and will not scratch under everyday use.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <% @materials.where(:material_type => "Granite").each do |material| %>
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-3 col-lg-3">
              <div class="material-tile-wrapper">
              <%= link_to image_tag("materials/#{material.photo}", class:"materials-tile") %>
              <p><%= "#{material.name}"%></p>
              </div>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="materials-end-section">
    <p>Having trouble deciding? Feel free to <%= link_to "get in touch", contact_path %> with us. We can help you find a custom style.</p>
  </div>
</div>
